{"word":"δυσμαθής","slug":"δυσμαθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δυσμαθής</b></el> <el>(δυς-μᾰθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μανθάνω'><el>μανθάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>hard to learn</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>δ. ἰδεῖν</el> <i>hard to know</i> at sight, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <el>τὸ δυσμαθές</el> <i>difficulty of knowing</i> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>slow at learning</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>δυσμαθῶς ἔχειν</el> to be <i>so</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}